A HLAPI library for Open Computers 2: Reimagined. Only tested on a custom 1.21.1
build, but should work for 1.20.

Currently supports:
- device listing
- basic bus I/O (method invocations, etc...)
- redstone devices

See the header files in the `src` folder for documentation, and the
examples/utils folders for examples.

Run the `build.sh` script to build. Development was done inside OC2R, so the
build script uses `tcc`, there is no Makefile, and you must use the `import.lua`
built-in script to transfer the project into OC2R. Since the script only does
single file transfers, make sure to archive the `src` folder into a tar file and
transfer it instead.

To install, move the header files to a new /usr/include/tinyhl folder, and the
generated .so files to /usr/lib. Note that this hasn't been tested yet.